benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Remove tags from bundle

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios including removal of all tags, specific tags, and no-tagDef case (TC01, TC02, TC04); removal with headers (TC03)
Header validation and usage (TC03, TC08, TC14)
Error handling and appropriate status codes for invalid input or non-existent resources (TC05, TC06, TC07, TC09, TC10, TC14)
Query Parameters handling and validation (TC11, TC13)
Handling of large data sets and edge cases (TC12 with 1000 tags, TC16 with empty tagDef, TC18 timeout-related case)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested
Authorization path for 403 Forbidden is not covered (only 401 in TC09)
Caching behavior testing (ETag, Cache-Control) is absent
Soft-delete semantics (permanent vs logical delete) are not tested
Additional negative tests for mixed valid/invalid parameter combinations could be expanded
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to validate limit/offset behavior on large tag sets
Include a 403 Forbidden scenario to cover authorization edge cases beyond 401
Add tests around caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) to verify caching behavior
Introduce rate-limiting tests to ensure proper throttling under load
Document and test soft-delete semantics if applicable (permanent vs logical deletion)
Extend negative parameter tests to cover more mixed scenarios and edge cases
